         <div type="translation" xml:space="preserve"><head>Translations</head>
            <div  type="translation" source="#gl-jmr1983" xml:lang="de"><p>Salo des Alexander, 45 (Jahre); Jesus des Alexander, 8 (Jahre); Marin des Tryphon, 87 (Jahre). </p></div>
            <div type="translation" source="#edd" xml:lang="en"><p>Salo, <supplied reason="subaudible">daughter</supplied> of Alexandros, aged 45; Jesus, <supplied reason="subaudible">son</supplied> of Alexandros, aged 8; 
               Marin, <supplied reason="subaudible">daughter</supplied> of Tryphon, aged 87.</p></div>
       </div>
         
         <div type="commentary">
            <head>Commentary</head>
            <p>The names indicate a Jewish family whose stele may, therefore, have originally
                    stood in the West Necropolis, see on <ref type="inscription">A10900</ref>. 
                For a detailed discussion see Lüderitz. The date is unlikely to be
                    later than the Jewish Revolt of C.E. 115.</p>
         </div>
         
